OL,3,CWe must give youngsters way out of
OL,4,Cviolence, says Cleverly amid knives
OL,5,Ccrackdown
OL,7,FThe Home Secretary has defended the
OL,8,FGovernment's record on tackling knife
OL,9,Fcrime as he announced next steps to
OL,10,Fban zombie-style knives.
OL,12,FFresh legislation is set to be
OL,13,Fintroduced to Parliament on Thursday,
OL,14,Fwhich James Cleverly said seeks to
OL,15,F"close that loophole" on outlawing the
OL,16,Fweapons.
