OL,3,CWe must give youngsters way out of
OL,4,Cviolence, says Cleverly amid knives
OL,5,Ccrackdown
OL,7,F"When I became Home Secretary, I made
OL,8,Fthe immediate decision to go further
OL,9,Fto put forward this secondary
OL,10,Flegislation to support what we've
OL,11,Falready done to make the possession of
OL,12,Fzombie knives illegal and to close
OL,13,Fthat loophole.
OL,15,F"So I'm very pleased we're taking
OL,16,Faction now and we'll be determined to
OL,17,Fget these knives off the streets."
