OL,3,CWe must give youngsters way out of
OL,4,Cviolence, says Cleverly amid knives
OL,5,Ccrackdown
OL,7,FThe Government is also seeking to
OL,8,Ftoughen the penalties for people
OL,9,Fpossessing banned weapons by
OL,10,Fincreasing a maximum sentence from six
OL,11,Fmonths to two years.
OL,13,FLabour's shadow home secretary Yvette
OL,14,FCooper said: "Six Tory home
OL,15,Fsecretaries have promised these
OL,16,Fchanges, and still they don't go
OL,17,Fanywhere near far enough and don't
OL,18,Fmatch Labour's plans for a
OL,19,Fcomprehensive ban.
